25 Sen Floor Amend 2
LOST
Senators Jackson of the 41st and Hatchett of the 50th offered the following amendment #2:
Amend the Senate Committee on Regulated Industries substitute to HB 54 (LC 52 0844S):
By inserting between lines 162 and 163 the following:
SECTION 6A.
Said title is further amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
“43-34-34.1.
(a) As used in this Code section, the term:
(1) ‘Institution’ means a hospital licensed by the Department of Community Health and
its affiliated clinics, a board approved medical school, or a federally qualified health
center; provided that such institution has the capacity, personnel, and experience to
educate, supervise, and assess international medical graduates and carries medical
malpractice insurance covering international medical graduates employed by such
institution for the duration of employment.
(2) ‘International medical graduate’ means a physician who has received a degree of
doctor of medicine or its equivalent from a medical school outside of the United States
eligible for Educational Commission for Foreign Medical Graduates certification and has
been licensed or otherwise authorized to practice in a jurisdiction outside of the United
States.
(3)’Limited license’ means a license to practice medicine issued to an international
medical graduate employed at an institution and limited to providing healthcare services
in a health professional shortage area or medically underserved area or to a medically
underserved population or limited to teaching at a board approved medical college or its
affiliated clinic in this state. Such license shall be valid for up to two years and may be

